Questions:
What is the primary goal of the research study described in the consent form?
A) To assess the effectiveness of a new chemotherapy drug for head and neck cancer patients;
B) To evaluate the impact of triple pre-rehabilitation on patients undergoing radiotherapy for head and neck cancer;
C) To compare different surgical techniques for head and neck cancer treatment;
D) To investigate the psychological effects of radiotherapy on patients with head and neck cancer.

Correct answer: B

What will happen if you choose to withdraw from the "Effect of triple pre-rehabilitation on radiotherapy for head and neck cancer patients" study?
A) You will be required to pay for any treatments received during the study;
B) Your medical treatment and rights at Tianjin Medical University Cancer Institution and Hospital will be negatively affected;
C) Your participation in other clinical studies will be restricted;
D) Your current and future medical treatment and rights will not be affected, and you can withdraw at any time without any reason.
Correct answer: D

Which of the following is considered the experimental intervention in this study?
A) Standard radiotherapy for head and neck cancer patients;
B) Triple pre-rehabilitation intervention consisting of exercise, nutrition, and psychology before and during radiotherapy;
C) Weekly WeChat follow-ups for standard medical advice;
D) Use of elastic bands for physical exercise as part of standard care.

Correct answer: B) Triple pre-rehabilitation intervention consisting of exercise, nutrition, and psychology before and during radiotherapy.

What alternative options are available to patients who choose not to participate in the triple pre-rehabilitation study for head and neck cancer patients undergoing radiotherapy?
A) Patients can opt for a standard radiotherapy treatment without additional interventions; 
B) Patients will be provided with a specialized alternative cancer treatment program;
C) Patients will receive a combination of chemotherapy and radiotherapy as an alternative;
D) Patients are required to participate in a different clinical trial focusing on surgical interventions.

Correct answer: A

If you experience any discomfort or have concerns about your rights as a participant in the study, whom should you contact?

A) The principal investigator of the study;
B) The Ethics Committee of Tianjin Cancer Hospital;
C) The Biomedical Ethics Committee of Peking University;
D) Your personal physician.

Correct answer: B) The Ethics Committee of Tianjin Cancer Hospital.
